{
  "texts": [
    "The number of resulting clusters (excluding noise) serves as our polysemy estimate: P (w) = |clusters(w)|.",
    "This approach has been validated for sense induction tasks [2,12].",
    "Methods Models and DataWe analyze four models from the Pythia suite [3]: pythia-70m, pythia-160m, pythia-410m, and pythia-1b.",
    "These models are trained on the Pile dataset [?]",
    "with identical data order, enabling controlled comparison across scales.For each model, we sample 30 checkpoints logarithmically spaced from initialization to final training step (∼ 10 5 steps)."
  ]
}